il society organisations, was held in Glasgow with the Minister of State for International Development, Desmond Swayne MP, on 26 February 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening","9","2015-06-02T15:10:01.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346954/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346954/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-05-27","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many organisations headquartered (a) in Scotland and (b) elsewhere in the UK have (i) applied for and (ii) been awarded funding through the UK Aid Match Scheme in each year since that scheme was introduced.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","8"
