"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229354","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-26","<p>There is a tradition of funding new memorials through public subscription. We support this and experience has shown that there are often other funders, including the private sector, happy and willing to fund new memorials.</p><p>The DCMS ​does additionally administer the DCMS Memorial Grant Scheme which makes grants towards the VAT incurred by charities and faith groups in the construction, repair and maintenance of public memorial structures. The scheme has a fixed budget of £0.5m per year.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-03-26T10:03:50.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229354/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229354/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-24","Mining: Monuments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will support the erection of memorials to miners who lost their lives whilst working in the pits during the First and Second World Wars.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","228931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229355","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-03-26","<p>While operating over Syria, UK Reapers conduct a range of surveillance tasks. No UK Reaper missions have been conducted in Syria other than for surveillance purposes.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-03-26T15:19:16.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229355/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229355/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-03-24","Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2015 to Question 222433, on Syria, whether UK Reapers in Syria are conducting (a) pattern of life analyses, (b) collateral damage estimates and (c) battle damage assessments.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","228913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229356","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-03-26","<p>Following a period of consultation, Host Nation Notification in connection with the European Infrastructure Consolidated Review was received on 7 January 2015 and responded to on the same day.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-03-26T12:01:30.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229356/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229356/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-03-24","RAF Croughton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 10 March 2015 to Question 226256, on RAF Croughton, what the dates were of the (a) Host Nation Notification and (b) Host Nation Response made in connection with the European Infrastructure Consolidated Review.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","228912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229357","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-03-26","<p>We thank the French Government for making the offer to award the Legion d'Honneur to all those UK Servicemen who were involved in the liberation of France in 1944. So far the Ministry of Defence has passed in excess of 2,500 applications to the French Authorities.</p><p>We continue to receive and process applications on a daily basis and this week we anticipate a further 200 applications will be passed across to the French Authorities.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-03-26T10:05:45.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229357/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229357/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-03-24","Veterans: Military Decorations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made on the awarding of the Légion d'honneur to veterans of the Second World War.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","228914"
