"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229069","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-03-26T09:22:34.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229069/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229069/answer","PQ 228779 ONS 122.pdf","PQ 228779 ONS 122.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - Parkinson Disease Death","ONS Letter to Member - Parkinson Disease Death","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229069/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-23","Parkinson's Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people died of Parkinson's disease in England in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","228779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229070","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-03-26","<p>A copy of the Ex-UK Coal Concessionary Fuel Scheme Rules following the 15<sup>th</sup> November 2013 announcement was placed in the Libraries of the House.</p><p>As at 24 March 2015 the Government are meeting the solid fuel and cash in-lieu entitlement of 1,323 former UK Coal miners and their beneficiaries who had lost their entitlement as a result of the restructure of UK Coal in July 2013.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-03-26T15:51:03.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229070/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229070/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-03-23","Fuels: Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, with reference to the Treasury's announcement entitled Chancellor intervenes to honour fuel allowance benefits of ex-miners, published on 15 November 2013, if he will place in the Library the full criteria used in making decisions on concessionary fuel payments for former miners who worked in private-sector mines; and how many former miners received concessionary fuel payments as a result of that announcement.","false","Biography information for Joan Walley","Stoke-on-Trent North","Joan Walley","228648"
