"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229080","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>This information is not available. Companies with income from property cannot deduct interest as an expense against their property income as they are within the loan relationships regime.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-26T09:34:58.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229080/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229080/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-23","Companies: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many rental companies claimed interest relief in each year since May 2010; and how much such relief was awarded in each such year.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","228795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229081","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Government has received no representations from contractors on this matter.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-26T09:40:07.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229081/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229081/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-23","Public Sector: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he received from existing large public-sector contractors before deciding to remove VAT charges for private-sector bidders on public-sector contracts.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","228814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229082","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>There are no plans to remove VAT in relation to off-the-shelf ICT purchasing and thus no assessment has been made.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-26T09:45:02.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229082/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229082/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-23","Public Sector: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of removing VAT charges for private-sector bidders on public-sector contracts on drives to increase off-the-shelf ICT purchasing.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","228815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229083","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>Synnex-Concentrix UK Limited is paid on a payment by results model on the basis of savings to public finances from correcting tax credit claims. Payments to Concentrix are also based on the quality and accuracy of their work. The model provides for adjustments for mandatory reconsiderations.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The mandatory reconsideration process is set out as part of HMRC’s contract with Synnex-Concentrix UK Limited.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Tax credits claimants can discuss a mandatory reconsideration of a decision to amend a tax credits award by contacting Synnex-Concentix UK Limited on 0345 600 3130.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","228744","2015-03-26T10:07:01.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229083/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229083/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-23","Concentrix","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 23 March 2015 to Question 226273, what directions have been issued by HM Revenue and Customs to Synnex-Concentrix UK with respect to its contract to process mandatory reconsideration of tax credit claims; and upon what results will Synnex-Concentrix UK be paid.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","228762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229084","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Department do not hold this information centrally. The information requested can only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-03-26T09:08:07.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229084/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229084/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-23","Research","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what research reports his Department has commissioned from external bodies between September 2010 and December 2014 has not been published; when each such report was commissioned; what the nature of the research commissioned for each such report was; from whom each such research report was commissioned; what the value of each such commission was; on what date each such report was received by his Department; for what reason each such research report has not yet been published; and when he plans to publish each such report.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","228843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229085","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-03-26","<p>We do not routinely publish internal business cases; this has been the practice under current and previous Administrations. We do publish Impact Assessment where appropriate.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2015-03-26T08:39:30.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229085/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229085/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-03-23","Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, for which spending announcements made by him or his Ministers since 1 September 2014 the relevant business case has not been made public; and for what reason each such case has not been published.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","228812"
